    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-04-01T10:48:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-04-01T10:48:00-05:00" n="316"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d316">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">714.1515/327: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul in Chargé of the Legation in Honduras</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lawton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-04-01T10:00:00-05:48">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 1, 1920—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 2—6:51 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>30. Department’s telegram February 28, 2 [<hi rend="italic">1</hi>] p.m. The
                    Foreign Minister informs me that under the indication of Mediator settlement
                    becomes practically an arbitration and if the question has to be decided by
                    means suggested, Honduras judges it necessary to celebrate previous treaty with
                    Guatemala in order to fix the conditions [of] such arbitration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lawton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
